 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-100 mb-4">Detailed Comparison</h2>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Pricing</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Preply has a lower entry price, with tutors available from around $5/hour. Verbling tutors tend to start at $12/hour or higher. That said, both platforms have tutors at every price level. Preply's larger tutor pool gives you more budget options, while Verbling attracts more premium, experienced tutors.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Tutor Selection</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Preply wins on volume with 50,000+ tutors covering virtually every language. Verbling has 10,000+ tutors with a strong focus on English. If you want sheer choice, Preply is hard to beat. If you want a curated experience with a focus on English learning specifically, Verbling is compelling.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Native Speaker Access</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Verbling was built with native-speaker access as a core feature, making it popular for accent coaching, pronunciation work, and business English with native speakers. Preply also has native English tutors available. Both platforms let you filter by accent, nationality, and proficiency level.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Flexibility</h3>
 <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Both platforms allow pay-per-lesson booking without forcing a subscription. Preply offers additional savings through its subscription model if you plan to take multiple lessons per week. Verbling keeps things simple with per-lesson pricing. Both have flexible scheduling with tutors available across all time zones.</p>
 </section>

